# Build output
build/
logs/
Testing/
.cache/
cmake-build-*/
out/

# IDE files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vs/
*.user
*.suo

# Compiled objects
*.o
*.obj
*.a
*.lib
*.so
*.dll
*.dylib
*.exe

# CMake generated
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
cmake_install.cmake
Makefile
compile_commands.json

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Claude Code local data (settings, worktrees, plans). Trailing /* (not /)
# so the negations below can re-include team-shared config.
.claude/*
# Team-shared Claude Code config that SHOULD be in version control:
#   settings.json — project-level hooks (e.g. PostToolUse drift check)
#   bump.json     — recipe consumed by the user-level /bump skill
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/bump.json

# ImGui layout state
imgui.ini

# imgui-node-editor per-canvas layout state (Phase 9E-3)
NodeEditor.json

# Dependency directories (fetched by CMake at build time)
external/glfw/
external/glm/
external/googletest/
external/assimp/

# Note: external/glad/, external/stb/, and external/dr_libs/ are NOT ignored —
# they contain vendored source files committed to the repo.

# Core dumps (root-level only — avoids matching engine/core/)
/core
/core.*

# Log files
*.log

# Profiling output
*.prof
perf.data*

# Windows debug symbols
*.pdb

# Audit tool cache and generated reports
.audit_cache/
docs/AUTOMATED_AUDIT_REPORT*.md
docs/AUTOMATED_AUDIT_REPORT*_results.json
# Trend snapshots are per-run diagnostic state (AUDIT.md §L9 / FIXPLAN I5).
# Rolling retention of N is driven by `audit.py --keep-snapshots N`;
# everything under this pattern remains developer-local.
docs/trend_snapshot_*.json
**/__pycache__/

# Launch-day drafts — tactical artefacts (announcement copy, go-live
# command runbook) intentionally kept developer-local. Unignore if you
# want to commit them post-launch as a historical record.
docs/LAUNCH_ANNOUNCEMENT.md
docs/LAUNCH_DAY_RUNBOOK.md
docs/LAUNCH_POSTS.md

# Secrets — defense in depth. We also run gitleaks; these patterns
# prevent accidental staging of common credential-bearing files in the
# first place. See SECURITY.md and the pre-open-source audit checklist.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.template
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.token
credentials.json
credentials.yaml
secrets.json
secrets.yaml
.aws/
.ssh/
id_rsa
id_ed25519
*.netrc

# Local audit tool state — per-user, not per-project
.audit_suppress.local
.audit_verified.local

# Audit artefacts — see docs/PRE_OPEN_SOURCE_AUDIT.md §7.
# Audit-session outputs (findings lists, discovery logs, fix plans,
# automated-run snapshots) are local to the maintainer's workflow and
# aren't shipped in the public repo. Automated JSON result files embed
# absolute filesystem paths from the run machine, which would leak the
# maintainer's layout if published; the .md snapshots are per-run and
# superseded by each subsequent run.
#
# Process/standards docs stay tracked (AUDIT_STANDARDS.md,
# tools/audit/AUDIT_TOOL_STANDARDS.md, tools/audit/README.md, the audit
# tool source itself). docs/PRE_OPEN_SOURCE_AUDIT.md is the active
# open-source launch checklist and stays tracked.
/AUDIT.md
/AUDIT_TOOL_AND_WORKBENCH_IMPROVEMENTS.md
/DISCOVERY.md
/FIXPLAN.md
docs/AUDIT_[0-9]*.md
docs/CODE_AUDIT_REPORT.md
docs/PHASE*_AUDIT*.md
docs/AUTOMATED_AUDIT_REPORT*.md
docs/AUTOMATED_AUDIT_REPORT*.json
tools/audit/*IMPROVEMENTS*.md

# Non-redistributable assets — kept locally for the maintainer's use,
# excluded from the public repo. See docs/PRE_OPEN_SOURCE_AUDIT.md §4.
#
# Texturelabs textures — texturelabs.org allows free use but
# *forbids redistribution* in other asset packs / repos.
assets/textures/Texturelabs_*
#
# Tabernacle / biblical project content — destined for a separate
# private repo for commercial Steam release; not part of the open
# engine.
assets/textures/tabernacle/
#
# everytexture.com textures — license permits free personal/commercial
# use but explicitly forbids redistribution. See ASSET_LICENSES.md.
assets/textures/everytexture-com-stock-rocks-*/
#
# Large CC0 assets that live in the milnet01/VestigeAssets repo and are
# pulled in via CMake FetchContent at configure time. Listing them here
# stops `git add` from re-introducing them to the engine repo when the
# maintainer has them locally for builds. Patterns mirror what's tracked
# in VestigeAssets/assets/textures/.
assets/textures/*_4k.jpg
assets/textures/*_4k.blend.zip
assets/textures/*_4k.blend/
